Kubernetes:

Kubernetes is open source container orchestration platform which is used to automate deployment, scaling, and management of containerized applications.

Advantages:

!- It automatically scales up the pods based on traffic load.
2. It deploys new code without downtime.
3. Built-in mechanisms to evenly distribute traffic between diff pods.
4. Self healing: It automatically replaces or restart the failed containers or pods.


Pod:

--> Pod is basically smallest deployable unit which represnt single instance of application.

Deployment:

--> deployment is basically kubernetes objects to manage the pods.



Kubernetes commands

Get pods
kubectl --kubeconfig stage.conf get pods | grep fdx

Describe pods 
kubectl --kubeconfig stage.conf describe pod direct-integration-platform-usbank-586dbd7cf8-cxfv6
 

get logs in file 
kubectl --kubeconfig stage.conf logs  fisglobaldirect-6f579dd587-vtsd7   >> fisglobal4.txt

edit the deployment file:
kubectl --kubeconfig stage.conf edit cm fdx-parser
kubectl --kubeconfig stage.conf edit deployment fdx-parser

rollout/ restart of deployment:
kubectl --kubeconfig stage.conf rollout restart deploy biltdirect

scale down pod:

kubectl --kubeconfig stage.conf scale deploy biltdirect --replicas=0

Describe configMap :
kubectl --kubeconfig stage.conf describe configmap direct-integration-platform-atlanta

To execute curl command in cluster:

Kubectl --kubeconfig stage.conf  exec -it fdx-parser-579bc74ffd-x5k8h sh

Then run curl command

 
kubectl --kubeconfig kube-stg-new.conf logs -f -l app=wellsconnections
 
kubectl --kubeconfig kube-stg-new.conf describe configmap direct-integration-platform-atlanta
 
kubectl --kubeconfig kube-stg-new.conf delete pod usaadirect-784465fcdc-z4dxb
 
 
kubectl --kubeconfig kube-stg-new.conf scale deployconnectivity-queue-manager-pcx --replicas=1
 
kubectl --kubeconfig kube-stg-new.conf get deployment direct-integration-platform-fiserv
 
Kubectl --kubeconfig stage.conf  exec -it chasedirect-77fdfff565-52sg6 sh
 
kubectl --kubeconfig kube-stg-new.conf get nodes -A
 
kubectl --kubeconfig kube-stg-new.conf get events | findstr "fiserv-direct-api-57f69f956b"
 
kubectl --kubeconfig kube-stg-new.conf rollout restart deploy chaseconnection
 
